President Obama has announced the new recipients of the National Medal of Science and National Medal of Technology and Innovation, which are the highest honors for achievement and leadership in the fields of science and technology. The recipients will receive their medals at a White House ceremony later this year. The National Medal of Science recognizes individuals who have made outstanding contributions to science and engineering, while the National Medal of Technology and Innovation recognizes those who have made lasting contributions to America's competitiveness and quality of life. The list of new recipients includes distinguished individuals from various universities and organizations across the country.